<table class="data-table">
    <thead>
        <tr><th>Branch</th><th>WE signal / artifact</th><th>Queryable on a live page today?</th><th>Mutates the page?</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td><strong>(a) DECLARED</strong></td>
            <td><code>we:capability-manifest/provider.ts:139</code> (the <code>CapabilityManifest</code>
                interface: <code>specVersion</code> / <code>conformanceLevel</code> L0–L2 / <code>features</code>);
                shipped as a static <code>export const manifest</code> (<code>provider.ts:129</code>,
                <code>MANIFEST_EXPORT_NAME</code>)</td>
            <td><strong>No.</strong> It is a build-time export convention; no app ships a runtime-queryable
                manifest yet (<code>we:capability-manifest/check.ts:107</code>, <code>IMPLEMENTATION_MANIFESTS</code>
                is empty)</td>
            <td>No</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><strong>(b) PROBED</strong></td>
            <td>The scoped custom-element registry: <code>we:plugs/webregistries/declarativeRegistry.ts:39</code>
                (<code>REGISTRY_SCRIPT_TYPE = 'registry'</code> → <code>document.querySelectorAll('script[type="registry"]')</code>),
                <code>:279</code> (<code>SCOPED_REGISTRY_KEY</code> symbol on hosts), <code>:292</code>
                (<code>getActiveRegistryResult()</code>). The webexpressions binding layer
                (<code>we:plugs/webexpressions/index.ts:75</code>, <code>applyPatches()</code>) and its
                <code>we:plugs/webexpressions/CustomTextNodeRegistry.ts:46</code> — but these are
                injector-internal, <strong>no public global marker</strong></td>
            <td><strong>Partly.</strong> The declarative-registry markers are DOM/symbol-queryable; the
                webexpressions binding has no public probe surface, only injector-chain access</td>
            <td>No</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><strong>(c) VERIFIED</strong></td>
            <td>The conformance vector corpus (<code>we:conformance-vectors/schema.ts:53</code>,
                <code>ConformanceVector</code>) + a runner (<code>we:wrapper-conformance/runner.ts:62</code>,
                <code>runVector()</code>). WE holds the corpus + schema only; the runtime driver lives in
                FUI/plateau (per #899)</td>
            <td>Yes (a suite can run)</td>
            <td><strong>Yes.</strong> The runner creates DOM containers, renders the subject, and dispatches
